♪ ALL THE LOVE THAT'S IN MY LIFE

04:44.762 --> 04:46.460
-HURRY! I NEED RESUSCITATION.

04:46.590 --> 04:48.244
-SLADE, STOP IT.
I'M ON DUTY.

04:48.375 --> 04:49.941
-SO KEEP YOUR EYES OPEN.

04:50.072 --> 04:52.422
-JUST GO GET WET AGAIN,
WILL YOU?

04:54.032 --> 04:56.252
-I GUESS THAT MEANS
I CAN'T GIVE YOU A GIFT
WHILE YOU'RE ON DUTY EITHER?

04:57.340 --> 04:59.429
-WHAT KIND OF GIFT?
WHERE IS IT?

05:01.779 --> 05:02.824
-THIS WAS MY MOM'S.

05:09.352 --> 05:11.615
SHE SAID I SHOULD KEEP IT
TILL I MET THE RIGHT GIRL.

05:15.837 --> 05:16.968
-[GASPS]

05:18.013 --> 05:19.754
JIMMY, THIS IS SO BEAUTIFUL.

05:26.151 --> 05:27.414
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

05:27.544 --> 05:29.720
-JUST SAY
YOU'LL NEVER TAKE IT OFF.

05:31.592 --> 05:33.898
SUMMER, YOU'RE
ON DUTY, REMEMBER?

05:35.117 --> 05:36.466
I'M GONNA GO SURF
UP THE BEACH.

05:36.597 --> 05:38.555
I'LL COME BACK
AROUND LUNCH AND SEE YA.

05:48.652 --> 05:50.785
-GARNER, WILL YOU RELAX?
YOU'RE IN HAWAII.

05:50.915 --> 05:53.701
YOU'RE ON VACATION.
ENJOY THE SUN. HAVE FUN.

05:54.658 --> 05:56.530
HAVE ONE OF THOSE
RUM AND COKES.

05:57.139 --> 06:00.316
DON'T WORRY.
WE'LL HANDLE THINGS
WITHOUT YOU.

06:00.447 --> 06:01.839
PLEASE HAVE A GOOD TIME.

06:01.970 --> 06:03.145
ALL RIGHT.
TAKE CARE.

06:04.799 --> 06:06.583
[HANGS UP PHONE]
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

06:21.032 --> 06:22.512
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

06:22.643 --> 06:24.601
-UH... HI, DAD.

06:25.297 --> 06:28.692
MY SCIENCE PROJECT--
FIBER OPTIC TECHNOLOGY.

06:28.823 --> 06:30.912
JUST THOUGHT I'D TRY IT OUT.
-COOL.

06:31.042 --> 06:32.870
-HI, HOBIE!
DID YOU FIND THAT MONEY

06:33.001 --> 06:34.785
YOU DROPPED OUTSIDE
THE WOMEN'S LOCKER ROOM?

06:34.916 --> 06:37.614
-UH... YEAH. I FOUND IT.
-GOOD.

06:37.745 --> 06:39.703
-HELLO.

06:39.834 --> 06:42.140
-I UM... I HAD
A HOLE IN MY POCKET.

06:42.271 --> 06:43.794
SOME MONEY FELL OUT.

06:43.925 --> 06:45.622
CAN I HAVE
MY SCIENCE PROJECT BACK?

06:45.753 --> 06:47.407
-I THINK I'LL HANG ON TO THIS
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY.

06:47.537 --> 06:49.583
WHY DON'T YOU BE A GOOD BOY
AND GO PLAY ON THE BEACH?

06:49.713 --> 06:52.020
[SIGHS]

06:52.150 --> 06:54.109
WOMEN'S LOCKER ROOM...

06:55.502 --> 06:56.938
NOT A BAD IDEA.

07:02.204 --> 07:04.598
-MATT!
-HEY, JACKIE!

07:04.728 --> 07:06.121
WHAT BRINGS YOU UP HERE?

07:06.251 --> 07:07.644
-OH, SUMMER WAS IN SUCH
A HURRY THIS MORNING

07:07.775 --> 07:09.994
WHEN SHE LEFT THE HOUSE,
SHE FORGOT HER LUNCH.

07:10.125 --> 07:12.344
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT TOWER SHE'S IN?
-I'LL FIND OUT FOR YOU.

07:12.475 --> 07:14.259
-OH, GREAT!
YOU'RE A DOLL.

07:16.566 --> 07:20.048
-[SIRENS WAILING]

07:23.747 --> 07:26.271
-MAN:
LIFEGUARD! HURRY!
MY WIFE FAINTED!

07:27.316 --> 07:28.752
PLEASE HURRY!

08:12.274 --> 08:13.623
-COME ON.
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

08:13.754 --> 08:15.277
YOU JUST SUFFERED
A LITTLE HEAT STROKE.

08:28.464 --> 08:32.599
-[CLANGING]

08:32.729 --> 08:35.253
-[LOCK BREAKS]

08:40.955 --> 08:44.001
-WE'RE CONDUCTING
A HOUSE-TO-HOUSE SEARCH
IN THE PALISADES,

08:44.131 --> 08:45.481
BUT THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE
HE MADE IT DOWN HERE.

08:45.612 --> 08:47.396
HE MIGHT BE
ON THE BEACH SOMEWHERE.

08:47.527 --> 08:50.617
-HOW DANGEROUS IS HE?
-EVER SEE
"SILENCE OF THE LAMBS"?

08:51.661 --> 08:56.057
JACOB KILMER
MAKES HANNIBAL LECTER
SEEM LIKE LITTLE BO PEEP.

08:56.187 --> 08:59.408
FOR THE PAST 17 YEARS
HE'S BEEN LOCKED UP

08:59.539 --> 09:01.932
AND HAS NOT RESPONDED
TO ANY SORT OF REHABILITATION.

09:17.034 --> 09:19.384
HE ESCAPED
FROM A MENTAL INSTITUTION,

09:19.515 --> 09:21.604
TERRORIZED AND TORMENTED
THE WOMAN WHO WAS SUPPOSED

09:21.735 --> 09:23.519
TO TESTIFY AGAINST HIM
IN A MURDER TRIAL.

09:23.650 --> 09:25.913
I'VE BEEN TRACKING
HIM FOR TWO YEARS,

09:26.043 --> 09:28.698
BUT EVERY TIME WE GET CLOSE,
HE FINDS A NEW WAY TO DISAPPEAR.

09:36.924 --> 09:38.795
-ALL RIGHT.
WHAT CAN WE DO?

09:38.926 --> 09:41.363
-I WANT TO CLEAR THE BEACH
FROM TOPANGA TO SANTA MONICA,

09:41.493 --> 09:43.626
FUNNELING EVERYONE
THROUGH A POLICE LINE
IN THE PARKING LOT.

09:45.715 --> 09:47.282
-ALL RIGHT. GOT IT.

10:10.087 --> 10:12.002
-[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

10:42.119 --> 10:43.599
-POLICE OFFICER:
WE ARE CLOSING THE BEACH

10:43.730 --> 10:45.601
FROM TEMESCAL CANYON SOUTHBOUND

10:45.732 --> 10:47.168
TO CHAUTAUQUA
BOULEVARD NORTHBOUND.

10:47.298 --> 10:49.387
THE TWO MAJOR EXITS
ARE STATE BEACH

10:49.518 --> 10:50.693
AND BAYWATCH HEADQUARTERS.

10:50.824 --> 10:52.434
-OKAY, WE'RE CLEARING THE BEACH.

10:52.564 --> 10:53.565
PLEASE MOVE
TO THE EXITS OVER THERE.

11:02.879 --> 11:04.054
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

11:27.425 --> 11:33.431
-[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

11:35.259 --> 11:36.913
-POLICE OFFICER:
OPEN THE BAG PLEASE, SIR.

11:37.479 --> 11:38.610
STEP RIGHT THROUGH HERE.

11:58.587 --> 11:59.849
-[GASPS]

12:06.726 --> 12:08.336
-HI. EXCUSE ME,
BUT I'M SORRY,

12:08.466 --> 12:10.425
WE HAVE TO ASK EVERYBODY
TO PLEASE LEAVE THE BEACH.

12:10.555 --> 12:12.427
-WHY? IT'S SUCH A BEAUTIFUL DAY.

12:12.557 --> 12:13.863
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY
BE THE PROBLEM?

12:13.994 --> 12:15.517
-WELL, I DON'T KNOW.

12:15.647 --> 12:17.606
THEY JUST ASKED EVERYBODY
TO PACK UP THEIR THINGS

12:17.737 --> 12:18.694
AND PLEASE EXIT
TO THE PARKING LOT.

12:18.825 --> 12:20.304
-AH, PITY.

12:20.435 --> 12:22.785
I WAS SO ENJOYING
MYSELF HERE ON THE BEACH.

12:34.362 --> 12:37.017
-RADIO:
DO YOU COPY?
PARAMEDICS ARE ON THEIR WAY.

12:37.147 --> 12:38.322
OVER.

12:41.456 --> 12:42.587
-EXCUSE ME...

13:02.129 --> 13:03.870
-JOHN, LET ME TALK
TO MITCH RIGHT AWAY.

13:04.000 --> 13:06.829
-BUT YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND--
MY DAUGHTER IS A LIFEGUARD!

13:06.960 --> 13:08.831
-I'M SORRY.
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO STAY HERE.

13:10.050 --> 13:11.529
-SLOAN, YOU WANT
TO COME WITH ME?

13:11.660 --> 13:13.270
WE FOUND SOMETHING
IN THE STORM DRAIN

13:13.401 --> 13:14.924
THAT I THINK
YOU SHOULD TAKE A LOOK AT.

13:22.279 --> 13:25.805
-[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

13:31.071 --> 13:32.463
-POLICE OFFICER:
SEE YOUR BAG PLEASE, SIR?

13:48.871 --> 13:52.875
-GET IN,
CLOSE THE DOOR,

13:53.006 --> 13:54.398
AND PUT BOTH HANDS
ON THE WHEEL.

14:22.426 --> 14:25.125
-[RADIO CHATTER]

14:25.255 --> 14:26.822
-PLEASE TILT
THE REAR-VIEW MIRROR

14:26.953 --> 14:28.258
SO I CAN SEE
OUT THE WINDSHIELD.

14:32.567 --> 14:34.308
-RADIO:
ALL AVAILABLE LIFEGUARD UNITS
SOUTH OF SANTA MONICA PIER...

14:34.438 --> 14:36.614
-THE POLICE HAVE ALL THE EXITS
FROM THE BEACH SEALED.

14:37.702 --> 14:40.183
-THEY WON'T STOP YOU.
YOU'RE A LIFEGUARD,

14:40.314 --> 14:42.011
AND I NEED
YOU TO RESCUE ME.

14:45.101 --> 14:46.624
THAT'S SUFFICIENT.
THANK YOU.

14:48.017 --> 14:49.236
YOU MAY START
THE TRUCK NOW.

14:52.848 --> 14:54.763
GIVE IT SOME GAS, PLEASE.

15:02.553 --> 15:04.642
NOW DRIVE TOWARD THE PIER.

15:06.862 --> 15:09.082
-RADIO:
233, 233, THIS IS 236.

15:09.212 --> 15:11.823
GO TO CHANNEL 12. REPEAT--
GO TO CHANNEL 12. OVER.

15:11.954 --> 15:15.218
-KEEPING BOTH HANDS
ON THE WHEEL WILL BE
TO YOUR BENEFIT.

15:19.135 --> 15:21.224
I LIKE TO KEEP INFORMED.

15:21.355 --> 15:23.444
-RADIO:
ROGER. MAINTAIN
YOUR PATROL AND STAND BY.

15:24.184 --> 15:26.055
-SLOAN:
ALL RIGHT. WE KNOW
HE'S ON THE BEACH.

15:26.186 --> 15:28.536
LET'S MAKE SURE
HE DOESN'T GET AWAY THIS TIME.

15:32.105 --> 15:35.673
-211-L, KMF-295.
COME IN, RON.

15:35.804 --> 15:37.197
-SEND YOUR TRAFFIC, MITCH.

15:37.327 --> 15:39.373
-RON, I WANT
HOBIE OFF THE BEACH A.S.A.P.

15:39.503 --> 15:41.114
SEND THE CLOSEST UNIT
TO COME PICK HIM UP.

15:41.244 --> 15:43.768
-KMF-259, 217-L.

15:43.899 --> 15:45.988
MITCH NEEDS BACK UP
AT THE STORM DRAIN, OVER.

15:48.991 --> 15:51.776
LIEUTENANT HOLDEN?
PLEASE COME BACK.

15:52.952 --> 15:54.431
LIEUTENANT HOLDEN?

15:57.347 --> 16:00.916
-IF YOUR VOICE OR YOUR WORDS
BETRAY ME, LIEUTENANT HOLDEN,

16:01.047 --> 16:03.353
I WILL SILENCE THEM FOREVER.

16:05.268 --> 16:07.140
SAY YOU'RE RESPONDING
TO A MINOR EMERGENCY,

16:07.270 --> 16:09.098
NOTHING THAT REQUIRES BACKUP.

16:14.495 --> 16:16.888
-THIS IS 217-L.
GO AHEAD, MITCH.

16:17.019 --> 16:19.979
-STEPHANIE, CAN YOU COME
OVER TO THE STORM DRAIN
RIGHT AWAY, PLEASE?

16:20.109 --> 16:21.502
-I'M SORRY, MITCH.
I'VE GOT A CODE--

16:22.590 --> 16:26.333
-NO CODES.
SIMPLE ENGLISH, PLEASE.

16:26.463 --> 16:27.899
-CODE WHAT?
YOU CUT OUT ON ME.

16:28.030 --> 16:30.250
-I'VE GOT A LOST BOY
IN THE TRUCK WITH ME.

16:30.380 --> 16:33.122
HE'S PRETTY SCARED.
I'M GONNA TAKE HIM
TO FIND HIS PARENTS.

16:33.253 --> 16:35.037
-WHY DON'T YOU JUST
TURN THE TRUCK AROUND

16:35.168 --> 16:36.647
AND DRIVE THE BOY
OVER HERE?

16:36.778 --> 16:38.954
-TELL HIM THE BOY
IS MUCH TOO SCARED.

16:39.085 --> 16:40.434
[PRETENDS TO CRY]

16:40.564 --> 16:42.958
-I'M SORRY, MITCH.
HE'S REALLY SCARED.

16:43.089 --> 16:45.352
I'VE GOT TO DRIVE
AND FIND HIS PARENTS.

16:45.482 --> 16:48.224
-[KILMER CRYING]

16:50.661 --> 16:55.188
THAT WAS GOOD, STEPHANIE.
YOU'RE EARNING MY RESPECT.

16:56.667 --> 16:58.800
-KILMER CAME THROUGH
THE STROM DRAIN, ALL RIGHT.

16:58.930 --> 17:01.803
MAYBE HE GOT OFF THE BEACH
BEFORE WE SET UP OUR PERIMETER.

17:01.933 --> 17:03.370
-I DON'T THINK SO.
HAVE YOUR MEN BLOCK

17:03.500 --> 17:05.111
THE TOP OF THE INCLINE
SOUTH OF HEADQUARTERS.

17:05.241 --> 17:07.635
I THINK KILMER IS
IN THAT LIFEGUARD TRUCK

17:07.765 --> 17:08.766
WITH ONE OF MY PEOPLE.

17:08.896 --> 17:10.464
-WHY IS THAT?

17:10.594 --> 17:12.640
-WE DON'T DRIVE AROUND
LOOKING FOR KIDS' PARENTS.

17:12.770 --> 17:15.251
WE HOLD THE KIDS
AT HEADQUARTERS TILL
THE PARENTS COME PICK THEM UP.

17:15.382 --> 17:17.165
-WAIT. I'M COMING WITH YOU.

17:17.297 --> 17:19.907
THIS IS SLOAN.
WE GOT A POSSIBLE
HOSTAGE SITUATION.

17:20.039 --> 17:22.867
-RADIO:
208, THIS IS 236.
EVAC FROM TEMESCAL CANYON

17:22.998 --> 17:24.868
TO CHAUTAUQUA
IS STILL IN EFFECT, OVER.

17:31.615 --> 17:33.835
-STOP.

17:33.965 --> 17:37.360
-RADIO:
REPEAT-- ALL UNITS
KEEP CLEAR AND STAND BY.

17:38.274 --> 17:40.276
-GO! DEPLOY! MOVE!

17:44.411 --> 17:46.978
-IT MUST'VE BEEN
SOMETHING YOU SAID.

17:47.109 --> 17:49.981
[CLICKS TONGUE]
TURN AROUND.

17:50.112 --> 17:52.680
IF I DON'T GET OFF THIS BEACH,
NEITHER DO YOU.

18:07.173 --> 18:09.000
-POLICE OFFICER:
HOLD AT SAFE DISTANCE.
STAY RIGHT WITH HIM.

18:09.131 --> 18:10.872
BE CAREFUL.
DON'T PROVOKE HIM.

18:23.232 --> 18:25.365
-RADIO:
PARAMEDICS ARE ON THEIR WAY.

18:31.110 --> 18:32.502
-THERE DOESN'T SEEM
TO BE ANY REASON

18:32.633 --> 18:34.548
TO STAY DOWN HERE.

18:34.678 --> 18:36.854
-THERE'S NO WAY OUT.
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GIVE YOURSELF UP?

18:36.985 --> 18:38.552
NO ONE'S GONNA HURT YOU.

18:38.682 --> 18:40.597
-PAIN MEANS DIFFERENT THINGS
TO DIFFERENT PEOPLE.

18:40.728 --> 18:42.860
-RADIO:
ALL UNITS KEEP CLEAR.
CHECK CHANNEL THREE.

18:42.991 --> 18:45.211
-STOP IN FRONT
OF THAT TOWER RAMP.

18:49.389 --> 18:51.565
-PATCH ME THROUGH
TO SUMMER'S TOWER. HURRY!

18:57.614 --> 18:59.268
-SLIDE OVER ME
AND GET OUT.

19:03.533 --> 19:05.405
-SUMMER, GET OUT
OF THE TOWER RIGHT NOW.

19:12.847 --> 19:14.240
OVER THE RAIL!

19:16.155 --> 19:18.548
-IT'S TOO LATE. HE'S ALREADY
BACKING UP THE RAMP
WITH STEPHANIE.

19:19.419 --> 19:22.030
-SUMMER.
-I'VE GOTTA HELP HER.

19:28.950 --> 19:31.431
-KILMER, THERE'S NO WAY
OUT OF THIS.

19:31.561 --> 19:34.347
LET THE LIFEGUARD GO,
AND NO ONE WILL HURT YOU.

19:35.957 --> 19:40.222
-IF ALL YOUR VEHICLES
AND PERSONNEL AREN'T
OFF THE BEACH IN 30 SECONDS,

19:40.353 --> 19:42.529
I'LL SHOOT HER LEG
THROUGH THE FEMORAL ARTERY!

19:42.659 --> 19:44.400
SHE'LL BLEED TO DEATH!

19:46.359 --> 19:48.187
-SLOAN OVER RADIO:
IF THE SHOT'S CLEAR,
SMOKE HIM.

19:48.317 --> 19:50.058
-WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

19:50.189 --> 19:52.539
YOU'RE FIRST RESPONSIBILITY
IS THE SAFETY OF MY PEOPLE.

19:52.669 --> 19:54.628
-MY RESPONSIBILITY
IS TO DROP THAT MANIAC.

19:54.758 --> 19:56.673
-IT'S MY BEACH, PAL.
I'M IN CHARGE HERE.

19:56.804 --> 19:59.023
-NO. ONCE HE GETS
INTO THAT TOWER,
HE'LL BE IN CHARGE.

19:59.154 --> 20:00.982
-15 SECONDS!

20:09.425 --> 20:10.992
-RADIO:
I CAN'T GET A CLEAR SHOT.

20:11.819 --> 20:13.168
-FIVE SECONDS!

20:13.299 --> 20:14.778
-TELL YOUR MEN
TO CLEAR THE BEACH! NOW!

20:14.909 --> 20:16.040
-[GASPING]

20:25.789 --> 20:27.400
-[LAUGHING]

20:50.031 --> 20:51.511
-[BOTH YELP]

21:07.440 --> 21:08.789
-WHO THE HELL IS THAT?

21:17.667 --> 21:18.842
-IT'S SLADE.

21:21.018 --> 21:23.760
-WHOEVER SAID "THREE'S A CROWD"
DIDN'T HAVE THE RIGHT COMPANY.

21:43.345 --> 21:44.390
-AND YOUR NAME IS?

21:44.520 --> 21:45.652
-SUMMER.
-SUMMER...

21:45.782 --> 21:49.830
FALL, WINTER, SPRING.

21:52.136 --> 21:53.834
SHE WAS AN INDIAN
ON "HOWDY DOODY."

21:53.964 --> 21:55.575
A MARIONETTE, ACTUALLY.

21:55.705 --> 21:57.707
SHE COULD ONLY MOVE
WHEN HER STRINGS WERE PULLED.

21:58.578 --> 21:59.970
THAT SHALL DEFINE
OUR RELATIONSHIP

22:00.101 --> 22:02.321
FOR AS LONG AS
WE ARE TOGETHER.

22:03.365 --> 22:06.237
I WILL CONTROL
EVERYTHING YOU DO.

22:09.980 --> 22:14.507
FIRST, WE NEED TO SECURE
OUR LITTLE FORTRESS HERE.

22:19.033 --> 22:21.775
-NO ONE IS TO FIRE
WITHOUT A DIRECT ORDER FROM ME.

22:21.905 --> 22:24.647
-DAD! WHAT'S GOING ON?

22:24.778 --> 22:26.606
-MITCH, WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN
TO SUMMER AND STEPHANIE?

22:26.736 --> 22:28.259
-JUST TAKE IT EASY.
WE'RE ON IT. WE'RE ON IT.

22:28.390 --> 22:31.393
-WHAT'S THE KID DOING?
-NOTHING YET.

22:33.264 --> 22:34.657
HOLD ON.

22:35.528 --> 22:37.181
ONE OF THE LIFEGUARDS
IS COMING OUT.

22:41.229 --> 22:42.665
KID JUST CLIMBED
ONTO THE DECK.

22:50.107 --> 22:51.544
--SHH.

22:53.763 --> 22:55.374
-WHAT AN APPROPRIATE
PLACE TO BE.

22:55.504 --> 22:57.811
DON'T YOU THINK, STEPHANIE?

22:57.941 --> 23:00.117
[LAUGHS]

23:10.084 --> 23:11.607
-LIFEGUARD:
SHE'S CLOSING THE FLAPS.

23:12.869 --> 23:15.742
-WITH THE FLAPS CLOSED,
KILMER WILL HAVE BLIND SPOTS
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

23:15.872 --> 23:17.396
-TELL SWAT TO BE READY.

23:23.358 --> 23:25.621
-WHO GUARDS
THE LIFEGUARD'S LIFE

23:26.143 --> 23:29.103
WHEN THE LIFEGUARD'S LIFE
NEEDS GUARDING? HMM?

23:29.973 --> 23:32.367
[LAUGHS]

23:49.340 --> 23:50.994
-[SCREAMS]

23:54.563 --> 23:55.869
-SLADE!

23:58.567 --> 24:01.483
-UGH. THE KID'S BEEN SHOT!
-HE'S GETTING TO HIS FEET.

24:01.614 --> 24:04.051
-LOOKS LIKE A SHOULDER WOUND.
HOLD YOUR POSITION.

24:04.181 --> 24:06.183
-GET THE PARAMEDICS
IN A CALL CAR, RON.

24:07.446 --> 24:09.535
-THIS IS KMF...
-SLADE, IF YOU CAN HEAR ME,

24:09.665 --> 24:11.232
GET IN THE TRUCK.

24:12.189 --> 24:13.234
DON'T THINK ABOUT
ANYTHING ELSE, PAL.

24:13.364 --> 24:15.149
JUST GET IN THE TRUCK.

24:23.592 --> 24:24.637
-HE'S GETTING INTO THE TRUCK.

24:25.507 --> 24:27.683
-WITH THE FLAPS CLOSED,
KILMER'S VISION IS LIMITED.

24:27.814 --> 24:30.251
SEE IF YOU CAN GET A SQUAD
CLOSER TO THE TOWER.

24:30.381 --> 24:32.035
-OKAY PAL,
START THE TRUCK

24:32.166 --> 24:33.733
AND HEAD THIS WAY.

24:34.298 --> 24:35.778
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.

24:48.574 --> 24:50.532
-STEPHANIE:
LOOK, YOU DON'T
NEED BOTH OF US.

24:52.360 --> 24:54.057
WHY DON'T
YOU LET SUMMER GO?

24:55.015 --> 24:57.060
-INTERESTING SUGGESTION.

25:01.021 --> 25:05.852
-[BOTH SCREAMING]

25:15.862 --> 25:18.299
-[LAUGHS]

25:21.389 --> 25:23.957
-OH MY GOD. SUMMER!
-MOVE IN! MOVE IN!

25:30.659 --> 25:32.269
-GET IN THE TRUCK.

25:32.400 --> 25:33.923
-NO WAY!
NOT UNTIL SUMMER'S OKAY.

25:34.054 --> 25:36.535
-LOOK PAL, THIS ISN'T
MULTIPLE CHOICE, OKAY?

25:36.665 --> 25:37.971
YOU'RE OUTTA HERE.

25:40.669 --> 25:41.844
OKAY! GO!

25:52.072 --> 25:54.030
-LITTLE PEEPHOLES.

25:57.860 --> 26:00.820
SO WE CAN SEE
WHO COMES TO VISIT NEXT.

26:03.953 --> 26:05.085
OH...

26:12.875 --> 26:13.920
-[PHONE BEEPS]

26:16.139 --> 26:17.924
-KILMER:
WHOEVER THIS IS,

26:18.533 --> 26:21.275
HAVE THE POLICE TURN
AND RETREAT IMMEDIATELY

26:21.405 --> 26:24.670
OR I WILL SHOOT
ONE OF THESE YOUNG LADIES.

26:24.800 --> 26:26.541
-HOW DO WE KNOW
YOU HAVEN'T ALREADY?

26:28.064 --> 26:30.632
-SAY YOUR NAMES... NOW!

26:33.504 --> 26:35.245
-STEPHANIE HOLDEN.

26:36.943 --> 26:38.161
-SUMMER QUINN.

26:38.292 --> 26:39.598
-SUMMER.

26:42.513 --> 26:44.559
-CALL OFF THE SQUAD.
THEY'RE ALL RIGHT.

26:44.690 --> 26:47.170
HAVE THEM RETREAT
TO THE PARKING LOT.

26:51.044 --> 26:53.829
-I CAN SEE THE BEACH
IN ALL DIRECTIONS.

26:54.743 --> 26:57.224
IF ANYONE COMES NEAR
THIS TOWER AGAIN,

26:58.268 --> 27:00.009
THERE WILL BE
NO MORE WARNINGS.

27:01.707 --> 27:03.622
-LOOK, WE KNOW YOU HAVE
THE UPPER HAND.

27:03.752 --> 27:05.841
EVERYBODY REALIZES THAT.

27:07.756 --> 27:09.366
WE DON'T WANT ANYONE ELSE
TO GET HURT HERE.

27:09.497 --> 27:11.412
-YES. I AGREE.

27:11.542 --> 27:14.763
AND NO ONE WILL BE
IF MY INSTRUCTIONS
ARE CAREFULLY FOLLOWED.

27:14.894 --> 27:17.418
-HE WANTS A HELICOPTER
FULLY FUELED TO LAND

27:17.548 --> 27:19.681
IN FRONT OF THE TOWER RAMP
IN AN HOUR.

27:19.812 --> 27:21.988
I WANT OUR BEST
SHARP SHOOTER ON IT.

27:22.815 --> 27:24.991
IT'S ALWAYS A RISK,
BUT BY THE TIME WE GET TO HIM,

27:25.121 --> 27:26.340
HE MAY HAVE KILLED
BOTH OF THEM ANYWAY,

27:26.470 --> 27:27.820
SO WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES THAT MAKE?

27:28.429 --> 27:29.473
-WHAT THE HELL
DOES THAT MEAN?

27:29.604 --> 27:31.258
"WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES THAT MAKE?"

27:31.388 --> 27:33.347
-LET US DO OUR JOB, LIEUTENANT.
-THERE ARE OTHER CHOICES HERE!

27:34.087 --> 27:36.132
-IF SOMEONE'S DROWNING,
I'LL CALL YOU.

27:47.187 --> 27:50.538
-RON, GIVE ME A SCHEMATIC
OF THE OLD STORM DRAIN ASAP.

28:04.857 --> 28:07.207
-I WILL TAKE ONE OF YOU
WITH ME ON THE HELICOPTER.

28:07.903 --> 28:09.078
THE OTHER WILL STAY HERE.

28:12.038 --> 28:13.387
WHICH SHALL IT BE?

28:16.738 --> 28:18.653
-THAT'S PLASTIQUE, ISN'T IT?

28:19.610 --> 28:20.829
-WHAT?

28:22.352 --> 28:24.746
-AN EXPLOSIVE.
HE'S MAKING A BOMB.

28:24.877 --> 28:27.531
-THINK OF IT AS
A LIFE INSURANCE POLICY.

28:28.445 --> 28:31.710
IF I REMAIN ALIVE,
SO WILL WHICHEVER
OF YOU REMAINS HERE.

28:38.586 --> 28:40.719
[LAUGHS]

28:46.637 --> 28:48.465
-WE DON'T HAVE
THAT MUCH TIME.

28:48.944 --> 28:51.512
-WHEN THE HELICOPTER LANDS
AND KILMER MAKES HIS MOVE,

28:52.121 --> 28:53.993
WE BETTER BE THERE
WAITING FOR HIM.

28:54.123 --> 28:55.255
LET'S GO.

29:04.177 --> 29:08.877
-[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

29:34.381 --> 29:39.386
-[INDISTINCT]

32:08.927 --> 32:10.276
-ROTATE IT.

32:10.406 --> 32:12.452
-DAMN IT!
-WHAT?

32:16.978 --> 32:18.980
-WE'RE 10 FEET
SHORT OF THE TOWER.

32:19.676 --> 32:21.069
WE NEED TO BE
RIGHT UNDER IT.

32:21.940 --> 32:24.812
-LISTEN.
-IT'S THE CHOPPER.

32:25.987 --> 32:27.336
-WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

32:41.829 --> 32:43.787
-[HANDCUFFS CLANK]

33:20.737 --> 33:22.565
-HE SAYS THE BOMB
IS ON A TIMER

33:22.696 --> 33:25.481
AND IT'LL GO OFF
IN FIVE MINUTES
UNLESS HE DEACTIVATES IT.

33:26.352 --> 33:29.703
-WHICH I WILL DO
WHEN WE ARE SAFELY AIRBORNE.

33:30.182 --> 33:32.053
-WHICH HE WILL DO
WHEN WE'RE AIRBORNE.

33:32.184 --> 33:34.012
-TELL HIM HE DOESN'T
NEED THE BOMB.

33:34.142 --> 33:35.578
WE'LL GUARANTEE HIS SAFETY.

33:36.188 --> 33:38.451
-HE SAYS THAT'S
WHAT THE BOMB'S FOR.

33:50.550 --> 33:52.465
-DO YOU SEE HIM YET?
-NOT YET.

33:52.595 --> 33:55.424
BUT MY DAD WILL GET THERE.
I KNOW IT.

34:01.561 --> 34:02.866
-MITCH, THIS IS TOO DANGEROUS!

34:02.997 --> 34:04.868
I'M NOT GONNA
LET YOU DO THIS!

34:06.870 --> 34:08.350
-THERE'S NO OTHER CHOICE.

34:09.134 --> 34:10.351
DON'T WORRY.

34:10.483 --> 34:12.746
I'LL JUST MAKE
LIKE A LITTLE SANDWORM.

34:23.452 --> 34:27.326
-[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

34:44.864 --> 34:48.521
-NO SHOT EXCEPT
ON MY DIRECT COMMAND.

34:49.174 --> 34:50.043
-POLICE OFFICER:
ROGER.

34:57.878 --> 35:00.272
-IT DOESN'T MATTER TO YOU
WHETHER WE LIVE OR DIE, DOES IT?

35:00.402 --> 35:01.621
-ON THE CONTRARY.

35:02.448 --> 35:05.277
IF YOU DIE, IT PROBABLY MEANS
I'M DEAD ALREADY.

35:05.799 --> 35:07.888
THAT MATTERS
TO ME VERY MUCH.

35:14.851 --> 35:17.724
-DON'T YOU EVER CARE
ABOUT ANYBODY ELSE
BUT YOURSELF?

35:17.854 --> 35:22.120
-I'M FULL OF CARE.
THAT'S WHY I'M SO CARE-FUL.

35:22.685 --> 35:24.513
[LAUGHS]

35:34.393 --> 35:35.959
-THAT THING YOU'RE HOLDING
IN YOUR HAND...

35:36.960 --> 35:38.484
IT WON'T REALLY
DEACTIVATE THE BOMB, WILL IT?

35:40.486 --> 35:42.009
-YOU DON'T REALLY
WANT ME TO GIVE AWAY

35:42.140 --> 35:43.706
THE ENDING
OF THE STORY, DO YOU?

35:43.837 --> 35:45.534
IT WOULD KILL
THE SUSPENSE.

35:45.665 --> 35:48.058
[LAUGHS]

35:54.587 --> 35:57.372
LET'S HUG AND HOPE
IT'S NOT GOODBYE.

35:59.287 --> 36:01.942
-SUMMER, DO WHAT HE SAYS.

36:04.553 --> 36:06.164
-WISH US LUCK.

36:33.495 --> 36:35.671
NOW LET'S MAKE SURE
THOSE POLICE SNIPERS

36:35.802 --> 36:37.673
CAN'T SEPARATE
ME FROM YOU.

36:38.196 --> 36:41.416
COME ALONG, SUMMER.
UNDER THE BLANKET WE GO.

36:48.336 --> 36:50.512
-SLOAN:
DAMN. WE'LL NEVER
GET A CLEAN SHOT.

36:51.296 --> 36:54.908
TAKE NO ACTION.
REPEAT-- TAKE NO ACTION.

36:55.038 --> 36:56.475
-POLICE OFFICER:
ROGER.

37:06.528 --> 37:07.877
-THERE'S DAD!

37:08.008 --> 37:09.836
HE'S BY THE BOTTOM
OF THE RAMP.

37:16.146 --> 37:18.975
MY DAD'S OUT THERE.
-WHERE?

37:19.106 --> 37:20.934
-IN THE SAND
BY THE RAMP.

37:22.196 --> 37:23.371
-DAMN HIM.

37:24.242 --> 37:27.375
I REPEAT-- DO NOT SHOOT
EXCEPT BY MY COMMAND.

37:27.506 --> 37:30.726
-KILMER:
NICE AND SLOW.
WE DON'T WANT TO TRIP AND FALL.

37:30.857 --> 37:32.815
-[BEEPING]

38:01.975 --> 38:03.281
-YOU GO.
-YES, SIR.

38:48.804 --> 38:50.328
-HOLD YOUR POSITIONS,
MEN, THERE!

39:13.002 --> 39:14.656
-SUMMER, DEACTIVATE IT!

39:16.310 --> 39:17.703
-OH, STEPHANIE,
IT DOESN'T WORK!

39:17.833 --> 39:20.358
-OH! GET--
GET ME OUT OF HERE!

39:30.150 --> 39:33.719
[GASPING]
HELP.

39:42.771 --> 39:44.686
SUMMER! GET THE KEY
FROM THE COOLER!

39:46.209 --> 39:47.602
HURRY!

39:51.084 --> 39:52.128
-MITCH!

40:03.575 --> 40:04.837
-MITCH!

40:05.751 --> 40:08.710
-THE KEY! THE KEY!
-GET OUT OF HERE!
IT'S GONNA BLOW!

40:08.841 --> 40:10.625
-PLEASE HURRY UP!

40:15.108 --> 40:16.239
-GO! GO!

40:34.649 --> 40:36.042
-DAD!

40:42.614 --> 40:44.442
COME ON!
HURRY, DAD!

40:52.319 --> 40:53.799
COME ON!

41:10.337 --> 41:11.860
-[LAUGHS]

41:15.211 --> 41:19.607
-OH, MY GIRL!
OH GOD, HONEY. OH.

41:22.567 --> 41:26.571
-[LAUGHING]

41:31.184 --> 41:33.273
-GET HIM OUT OF HERE.
-LET'S GO, PAL.

41:34.143 --> 41:36.537
-[KILMER CONTINUES LAUGHING]

41:36.668 --> 41:39.671
-TELL YOUR TEACHER
TO GIVE YOU AN "A"
ON THE SCIENCE PROJECT.

41:44.937 --> 41:46.939
-SO HOW'S SLADE?
WHERE IS HE?

41:47.069 --> 41:49.507
-HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL.
HE'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.
